<h2>Captain's Log: Pirate Essentials</h2>
<div class="tale">
	<h5>By: Santiago</h5>
	<div class="text">
		Captain's Log: The Pirate Essentials<br />
by Santiago<br />
<br />
Got about halfway out into the bay b'fore I realized I'd forgot some things. Thar's certain supplies ye ought never go without: <br />
<br />
* fishin' pole (so ye never go hungry)<br />
* booze (so ye never go thirsty)<br />
* lantern (fer when it's dark -- also doubles as a grenade)<br />
* knife ('cause it just looks cool when ye carry it around in yer teeth)<br />
* sewin' kit (fer mendin' sails an' torn clothes)<br />
* handkerchief (fer givin' to ladies or fer wipin' up blood or blowin' yer nose)<br />
* sextant (fer when yer just plain lost)<br />
* lute (fer when the authorities demand that ye hand over yer ill-gotten pirate lute)<br />
* scissors (fer cuttin' bandages from cloth -- also doubles as an Oriental martial arts weapon)<br />
* bedroll ('cause them ship decks is hard to sleep on)<br />
* sword (to do unto others b'fore they do unto you)<br />
* armor ('cause it's always a good ideer to wear protection)<br />
* a wench (need I go into details?)<br />
* oil (fer refillin' lanterns or fer use in massages)<br />
* bandages (fer when ye get too fresh with the wench, an' she puts a knife in yer side)<br />
<br />
I'm prob'ly fergettin' a thing or two, but thar's the basics. Don't leave port without 'em!<br />
<br />
Anyways, I made one last stop at the village, an' actually saw some familiar faces! Thar was ol' William, for one. I asked him if he had turned evil -- he said no, an' looked surprised. Well, ye have to ask folks that nowadays! Seems like everyone ye know is bloody evil. An' I'll tell ye why...it's 'cause they practice magic! I always said it was the work o' the Devil. But did anyone listen? Heck no. Well, anyways, it turns out William ain't evil yet, since he gave me a bottle o' pirate rum (thankee, matey!).<br />
<br />
Ni'Vek an' Northstar was thar too, as well as Velaska. The lady looked awful fine, I mought add, an' thar was somethin' in her eyes what made me think she had somethin' naughty in mind. But she had to go (alas!), an' I was left with a bunch o' other folks I din't recognize who just ran around fightin' elementals. I s'pose some things never change!<br />
<br />
I was about to kidnap a lady (methinks her name was Natasha? So many women...hard to keep all the names straight), but then her husband showed up! Blast...seems like all the good fish has already been hooked an' pulled out o' the water. Anyways, the bloke was a right good chap...said his name was Elrios, an' that he was aimin' to join our Fleet! He thinks we're a good bunch o' folks, pleasant an' fun-lovin'. Hah! Wait 'til he gets bossed around by Tara -- that oughtter open up his eyes. *hee hee*<br />
<br />
Oh, it turns out the Fleet is gonna have a house of its own. I saw the house, though...the place is smaller than me boat. Not quite Everlight -- but I s'pose it's better than nothin'. One o' the cavalry folks wondered why the Storm Riders din't have a house o' their own. I said it was 'cause they weren't real stable! Get it? Stable! *har!*<br />
<br />
Well, anyways, it's high time fer me to set sail. Too much time in this ol' northern forest makes a fella crazy after a while...just look at Galventine! (*hee hee* just pullin' yer leg, matey). Nujel'm, here I come!
	</div>
